Financial Times is a big, fat lying liar who lies.

25
00:02:02,720 --> 00:02:06,000
China’s National Bureau of\h
Statistics came out with a\h\h

26
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:10,800
one-line statement saying that\h
China’s population grew in 2020.

27
00:02:11,440 --> 00:02:13,680
And Chinese state-run media were quick to publish\h\h

28
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:16,880
multiple articles denying\h
the Financial Times report.

29
00:02:17,920 --> 00:02:22,320
Of course, the actual population\h
data still hasn’t been released yet,\h\h

30
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:27,680
even though the census was supposed\h
to be published last month. Look,\h\h

31
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:34,400
Chinese statistics are an art, not a science.\h
And everyone knows you can’t rush art.

32
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:38,240
Especially now that they have to\h
fudge the numbers all over again\h\h

33
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:40,240
to refute that Financial Times report.

34
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:45,520
You know what else is an art? Reading\h
between the lines of Chinese propaganda.\h\h

35
00:02:46,480 --> 00:02:52,080
This Global Times article seems to indicate\h
that the census really did find that China’s\h\h

36
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:58,320
population was below 1.4 billion. But\h
they blamed that on a “statistical error.”

37
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:01,040
According to the Global Times,\h\h

38
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:07,200
China’s population didn’t really drop, it was\h
just never 1.4 billion in the first place.

39
00:03:08,160 --> 00:03:13,440
This is actually plausible. Some experts\h
have said for years that China’s population\h\h

40
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:19,120
estimates are inflated. One of the reasons\h
is that local governments are incentivized\h\h

41
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:23,600
to inflate their population numbers to get\h
more resources from the central government.

42
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:27,040
That’s a sign of a really functional system.

43
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:29,920
But the Global Times also said that China’s\h\h

44
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:34,160
population is likely to start\h
to decline as early as 2022.

45
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:40,080
Which is pretty interesting. Because previous\h
government estimates said that China’s\h\h

46
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:48,560
population would start to decline after 2027\h
or 2029. Suddenly moving that up to next year\h\h

47
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:52,720
shows this is a bigger problem\h
than the Party previously admitted.

48
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:57,120
So it’s quite possible China’s\h
population is already declining.\h\h

49
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:00,320
It’s just too politically sensitive to say it now.

50
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:05,520
But why are these population\h
statistics so politically sensitive?\h\h

51
00:04:06,240 --> 00:04:07,440
I’ll tell you after the break.

52
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,000
Welcome back.

53
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:16,320
One of the big dangers for the Chinese Communist\h
Party is that just as they get strong enough to\h\h

54
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:22,160
become the dominant global power, their internal\h
problems will trigger a crisis. And China’s\h\h

