00:04:22,160 --> 00:04:29,200
population decline is a big crisis. One that’s due\h
to the Chinese Communist Party’s one-child policy.

56
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:34,320
The first problem is that China now\h
has too many men and not enough women.\h\h

57
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:39,360
The common statistic is that there are more\h
than 30 million more men than women in China.

58
00:04:40,800 --> 00:04:45,600
That leads to things like sex trafficking\h
women from North Korea and Myanmar.\h\h

59
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,920
We’ve talked about that before on the show.

60
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:52,080
The second problem is that China is getting old,\h\h

61
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:57,760
fast. China’s working age population\h
has been falling since 2011.

62
00:04:58,640 --> 00:05:03,520
If this keeps going, China won’t have enough\h
workers to support its aging population.\h\h

63
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:07,600
And with China’s inadequate\h
pension and healthcare system,\h\h

64
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:11,600
that’s putting more pressure on\h
younger people to support older adults.

65
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:18,480
It’s also a big problem for China’s economy, which\h
has been built on having a huge supply of workers.

66
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:22,320
We’ve talked before about the\h
disasters of the one-child\h\h

67
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:27,440
policy, from the hundreds of millions\h
of forced abortions and sterilizations,\h\h

68
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:31,520
to the massive fines that were used\h
to make money for local governments.

69
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:37,840
And the tragic thing is, it turns out the\h
one-child policy was probably unnecessary.\h\h

70
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:44,400
China’s birthrate had already been falling\h
for a decade before the one-child policy.

71
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:50,320
But the Chinese Communist Party went ahead\h
with the one-child policy anyway, creating\h\h

72
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:56,160
an authoritarian social engineering project\h
that screwed up their population for decades.

73
00:05:57,120 --> 00:06:01,280
Birthrates started falling so fast that in 2016,\h\h

74
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:05,840
the Party changed their one-child\h
policy to a two-child policy.

75
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:11,520
Now this doesn’t mean there was more freedom.\h
It just meant that people were allowed to have\h\h

76
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:18,000
two kids instead of one. You still had to,\h
for example, get a permit to have a kid.

77
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:25,120
The massive bureaucracy created by the\h
one-child policy was still there. For example,\h\h

78
00:06:25,120 --> 00:06:31,520
the military, the police, and other state-owned\h
enterprises all have family planning units.

79
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:37,840
These family planning units do things like\h
monitor their female employees’ menstrual cycles.\h\h

80
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:40,880
And you thought your HR department was bad.

81
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:46,640
But while the two-child policy resulted in\h
an initial bump in the number of babies,\h\h

82
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:54,160
ultimately it hasn’t worked. In 2019, China’s\h
birthrate sank to the lowest level on record.

83
00:06:55,200 --> 00:07:00,320
It turns out that if you spend 35\h
years implementing a one-child policy,\h\h

84
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:06,080
a generation of only children don’t really\h
want to have more than one child themselves.\h\h

85
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:09,920
Especially because raising a kid\h
is getting more and more expensive.

86
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:15,120
The Chinese Communist Party knows this is\h
a problem. Which is why they’re starting\h\h

87
00:07:15,120 --> 00:07:20,080
to act like your mother when she asks you\h
why she doesn’t have grandchildren yet.

88
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:24,640
Earlier this year, the People’s\h
Bank of China released a report\h\h

89
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:28,800
calling for the central government\h
to “fully liberalize and encourage\h\h

90
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:33,680
childbirth,” meaning abandon restrictions\h
on how many children people can have.

91
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:39,760
Now this doesn’t mean there will be more\h
freedom. This is the Chinese Communist Party.\h\h

92
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:45,360
They’re going to use the full power of the\h
state to make sure people do what they want.

93
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:49,760
Does this mean that the Chinese Communist\h
Party will force people to have babies?

94
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:52,800
Should we get ready for China’s baby quotas?

95
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:55,280
I’ll tell you more after the break.

96
00:07:57,440 --> 00:08:01,760
Welcome back. Could the Chinese\h
Communist Party make people have babies?\h\h

97
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,840
Well, they’re definitely going to try.

98
00:08:04,640 --> 00:08:09,840
I’m not saying China’s going to go full Handmaid’s\h
Tale. They just don’t have enough women for that.

99
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:15,280
But the Party is already pivoting to\h
“encourage” people to have more children.

